Step 4: Set the $x^4$ term equal to zero and solve for $c$.

This means setting the coefficient of $x^4$ in the sum above to 0 . That coefficient comes from adding $5x^4 + (9c)x^4$, so set $5 + 9c = 0$. Then,
\begin{align*}
    (5+9c)&=0 \\
    9c&=-5\\
     c&=\dfrac{5}{-9}\\
     &=-\dfrac{5}{9}
\end{align*}

